rmation of cyclohexane the carbons do not lie in a single plane.";i:10;s:40:"Rather the carbon skele-ton is puckered.";i:11;s:110:"This conformation of cyclohexane is called the chair conformation be-cause of its resemblance to a lawn chair.";i:12;s:127:"If you have not already done so you should construct a model of cyclohexane now and use it to follow the subsequent discussion.";i:13;s:117:"The chair conformation has alternating axial up axial down so once you have that single axial substituent move on to.";i:14;s:82:"Alternate your axial substituents up and down all the way around your cyclohexane.";i:15;s:43:"Every carbon on the chair conformation has.";i:16;s:119:"Although the hydrocarbon cyclohexane is typically drawn as if it were flat in reality the structure is not flat at all.";i:17;s:79:"Most of the time the structure exists in what is called the chair conformation.";i:18;s:107:"This conformation is called the chair because it looks sort of like a reclining lounge chair as shown here.";i:19;s:14:"Answer 1 of 3.";i:20;s:107:"Stability of conformation decided by many factors like angle strain- any deviation from normal bond angles.";i:21;s:97:"Torsional strain- a pair of tetrahedral carbons attached to each other have their bond staggered.";i:22;s:67:"Any deviation from staggered arrangement is along with torsional s.";i:23;s:94:"A chair conformation is one of many conformations of a cyclohexane ring and it is most stable.";i:24;s:34:"It has equatorial and axial bonds.";i:25;s:122:"The equatorial bonds e are perpendicular to the axis of the ring while axial bonds a are parallel to the axis of the ring.";i:26;s:66:"Cyclohexane but make sure the Optimization limit is set to Normal.";i:27;s:115:"The greater flexibility of this molecule will be evident by the fact that MarvinSketch finds several conformations.";i:28;s:45:"The lowest energy form is the most important.";i:29;s:31:"This is the chair conformation.";i:30;s:48:"Carefully study this molecule by rotating it on.";i:31;s:262:"Chair conformation of cyclohexane is more stable than boat form because in chair conformaion the C-H bonds are equally axial and equatorial ie out of twelve C-H bonds six are axial and six are equatorial and each carbon has one axial and one equatorial C-H bond.";i:32;s:79:"This leads to a staggered conformation in chair form reducing torsional strain.";i:33;s:109:"The most stable conformation of cyclohexane is called chair conformation since it somewhat resembles a chair.";i:34;s:110:"In the chair conformation of cyclohexane all the carbons are at 1095ยบ bond angles so no angle strain applies.";i:35;s:117:"The ground state conformation of cyclohexane is a fully staggered conformation which is shaped somewhat like a chair.";i:36;s:105:"In this conformation there is no torsional strain at all and as we shall see later no strain of any kind.";i:37;s:68:"Cyclohexane is unique in being the only cyclic hydrocarbon which is.";i:38;s:95:"The different conformations are called conformers a blend of the words conformation and isomer.";i:39;s:52:"The chair conformation is the most stable conformer.";i:40;s:80:"At 25 C 9999 of all molecules in a cyclohexane solution adopt this conformation.";i:41;s:27:"Problem 47 Easy Difficulty.";i:42;s:100:"Conformation of cyclohexane contains centre of symmetry is A Chair B Boat C Half chair D Twist boat.";i:43;s:56:"The Newman projection for the twisted boat conformation.";i:44;s:51:"Cyclohexane can form three different conformations.";i:45;s:65:"Chair conformation is the most stable with the lowest energy and.";i:46;s:70:"The chair conformation is the most stable conformation of cyclohexane.";i:47;s:76:"I n chair cyclohexane there are two types of positions axial and equatorial.";i:48;s:131:"The axial positions point perpendicular to the plane of the ring whereas the equatorial positions are around the plane of the ring.";i:49;s:138:"These two chair conformations are the most common and comfortable of all the conformational possibilities available to a cyclohexane ring.";i:50;s:75:"Almost all of your work with cyclohexanes will involve chair conformations.";i:51;s:90:"Boat and Twist Boat Conformations There are additional conformations of cyclohexane rings.";i:52;s:45:"Boat twist boat and half-chair conformations.";i:53;s:73:"Half chair has five C atoms is one plane and one C atom out of the plane.";i:54;s:100:"Hence it has both eclipsing and bond angle strains and is the least stable conformer of cyclohexane.";i:55;s:131:"D Twisting the boat to the skew boat conformation moves the flagpole H atoms away from each other and reduces the eclipsing strain.";i:56;s:27:"What is Chair Conformation.";i:57;s:63:"Chair conformation is the most stable structure of cyclohexane.";i:58;s:34:"This is because it has low energy.";i:59;s:100:"Usually at room temperature around 25C all the molecules of cyclohexane occur in chair conformation.";}}